tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE Backtesting_Trading_Strategies (
    strategy_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_name VARCHAR(255),
    symbols TEXT[],
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE strategy_results (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_name VARCHAR(50),
    backtest_start_date DATE,
    backtest_end_date DATE,
    performance_metrics JSON
);

CREATE TABLE trade_data (
    trade_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    symbol VARCHAR(10),
    position_size INT,
    entry_price DECIMAL(10,2),
    exit_price DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE TradeData (
    trade_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    backtest_id INT REFERENCES Backtest(backtest_id),
    trade_symbol VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
    trade_quantity INT NOT NULL,
    trade_price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE trading_strategies (
    strategy_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_name VARCHAR(255),
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE strategy_data (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_id INT,
    data_date DATE,
    data_value FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE backtesting_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_id INT,
    result_date DATE,
    result_value FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE processing_queue (
    queue_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    strategy_id INT,
    queue_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE Trades (
  trade_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  strategy_id INT NOT NULL,
  trader_id INT NOT NULL,
  trade_date DATE,
  trade_symbol VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
  trade_quantity INT NOT NULL,
  trade_price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE MarketData (
  market_data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  trade_symbol VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL,
  market_date DATE NOT NULL,
  open_price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
  high_price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
  low_price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL,
  close_price DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE BacktestResults (
  result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  strategy_id INT NOT NULL,
  trade_id INT NOT NULL,
  result_date DATE,
  result_profit DECIMAL(10, 2) NOT NULL
);
